long acre
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:The strip of grass at each side of a formed country road used for free grazing;  esp. to graze the long acre, to turn stock out to graze along a road;  =long paddock, long meadow
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
